Preconditions:
- The input array `nums` is not null.
- The length of the input array `nums` is greater than or equal to 2.
- The elements in the input array `nums` are positive integers.
- The maximum value of the elements in the input array `nums` is less than or equal to 10^9.

Postconditions:
- The output is an integer representing the minimum deviation of the array.
- The minimum deviation is the maximum difference between any two elements in the array after performing some number of operations.
- The array after performing the operations has the minimum deviation.
- The array after performing the operations satisfies the conditions of the problem statement.
- The array after performing the operations is a valid array with positive integers.
- The array after performing the operations has the same length as the input array `nums`.